newsitem.title: AUSTRALIA: RTRS-Australia not in Pakistan wheat tender - AWB.
newsitem.headline: RTRS-Australia not in Pakistan wheat tender - AWB.

text.p: The Australian Wheat Board (AWB) did not intend to offer wheat at the Pakistan tender at this stage, Nigel Officer, AWB general manager international, told Reuters.
The AWB did not have the logistical spare space to offer in Pakistan's tender for 450,000 tonnes of Australian or U.S. wheat, he said.
AWB was fully booked in March with no spare capacity, while April was also virtually all committed, he said.
AWB was now focusing on May forward, he said.
The AWB announced earlier on Monday that its exports so far in the shipping year, which starts on October 1, totalled 6.55 million tonnes, up from 4.67 million tonnes a year before.
AWB has about 17 million tonnes of wheat for export from the 1996/97 season crop.
